properties.Name: Ameropan Oil
properties.description:
receives slurry oil by barge from Exxon Mobile in Joliet; also service terminal for asphalt products (Interstate Asphalt uses this terminal)
- slurry oil is a byproduct of refining heavy crude, essentially what remains after the “high-value “ material is removed from the crude. Either used locally as a cheap boiler fuel for industrial applications, as feed stock for carbon black, or transported by barge to New Orleans and shipped to Latin America or China. 0.7 gallons is generated for each barrel of crude oil.
in Jan 2005 a barge carrying clarified slurry oil from Exxon Mobile in Joliet to Ameropain Oil Terminal - (CSO) exploded and sank just after passing the cicero ave bridge

properties.Name: Koppers Inc
properties.description: Coal is carbonized to make coke and Koppers purchases a by-product of Coke-Coal tar. Koppers distills the coal tar and manufactures carbon materials and chemicals for the aluminum, steel, paint, plastic, wood-preserving, and carbon black industries. This plant: converts various crude tars into liquid pitch and other liquid products (creosote, refined tars, chemical oils and coal tar pitch). The wharf: receipt and shipment of petroleum products, residual oils, carbon black oil, tar etc by barge.
